Gold extended gains as two central
bank officials said European Central Bank President  Mario Draghi 
will hold talks with Bundesbank President Jens Weidmann in the
coming days in an effort to overcome the biggest stumbling block
to measures including bond purchases.  Gold futures for December delivery climbed 0.7 percent to
$1,630.50 an ounce at 1:36 p.m. on the Comex in New York.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
